 <div class="faq-list">
 {[
 {
 q: "What does it mean to have a life path number of 1?",
 a: "Life path 1 is the number of independence, initiative, and a drive to lead that most 1s didn't ask for. It just showed up.. People with this number are self-motivated, goal-oriented, and have a tendency to end up running things whether they planned to or not. The 1 is the first number in the cycle, which reflects how 1s move through the world: as initiators. The challenges include impatience, self-centered thinking, and difficulty accepting input from others. In astrology terms, the energy is closest to Aries - bold, direct, and a bit stubborn. The mind of a 1 is always scanning for the next move.",
 },
 {
 q: "Who should life path 1 marry?",
 a: "Life path 2 is the most recommended match for LP1. The 2's emotional depth and supportive nature balance the 1's independence without competing with it. Life path 3 and life path 6 are also strong compatibility options - the 3 brings creativity and lightness to the relationship, while the 6 brings warmth and stability. Life paths 1 and 8 can be challenging together: two ambitious, driven numbers in the same relationship often creates power struggles. Two life path 1 individuals together can work if both are secure enough not to keep score, but it requires genuine mutual respect.",
 },
 {
 q: "What are the weaknesses of life path number 1?",
 a: "The main weaknesses of life path number 1 are impatience, stubbornness, and a driven nature that can tip into selfishness when unchecked. 1s sometimes find it hard to delegate because they believe, often correctly, which makes it worse, that they'll do it better themselves. The tendency to domineer in group settings isn't always intentional, but it's real. The other common weakness is tunnel vision: when a 1 is locked onto a goal, they can neglect their love life, their health, and the people around them without noticing.",
 },
 {
 q: "What are the lessons of life path 1?",
 a: "The main lesson of life path 1 is that leadership doesn't require doing everything alone. 1s come into the world with a lot of natural ability, the focus, the self-motivation, the inner drive, but they often spend the first half of their life trying to prove they don't need anyone. The real work for this number is learning to combine that independence with genuine collaboration: being the initiator, taking charge, pursuing their own path - while also allowing others to contribute and keeping the ego in check. The 1 that learns this becomes effective rather than just relentlessly busy. Channelling that drive without burning bridges is the core growth edge for this number.",
 },
 {
 q: "What is the numerology chart position of the life path number?",
