 },
 {
 q: "Can life path 1 be a master number?",
 a: "No. The master numbers in numerology are 11, 22, and 33. A life path number only becomes a master number if the calculation produces one of those values before it's reduced to a single digit. Life path 1 is a standard single-digit number, not a master number. However, if your birth date reduces to 10, that 10 reduces to 1 and you're still a life path 1. The master number distinction applies to 11 (which doesn't get reduced to 2), 22 (not reduced to 4), and 33 (not reduced to 6).",
 },
